mplementation Chain\n\n**Endpoint Installation** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go`)\nThe API installer registers handlers for each verb by examining storage interfaces and creating routes:\n- Routes based on REST verb detection (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)\n- APIResource objects created with Verbs field populated from supported storage operations\n- Handler registration via `restful` web service framework\n\n**Handler Implementations** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/`)\n- `get.go`: GetResource() - implements \"get\" verb via Getter interface\n- `create.go`: CreateResource() - implements \"create\" verb via Creater interface  \n- `update.go`: UpdateResource() - implements \"update\" verb via Updater interface\n- `patch.go`: PatchResource() - implements \"patch\" verb via Patcher interface\n- `delete.go`: DeleteResource() and DeleteCollection() - implements \"delete\" and \"deletecollection\" verbs\n- `watch.go`: ListResource() with forceWatch parameter - implements \"list\" and \"watch\" verbs\n\n**Storage Interface Definitions** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/rest/rest.go`)\nREAL storage backend implementations must satisfy these interfaces to support verbs:\n- Getter - for GET (get)\n- Creater - for POST (create)\n- Updater - for PUT (update)\n- Deleter/GracefulDeleter - for DELETE (delete)\n- CollectionDeleter - for DELETECOLLECTION (deletecollection)\n- Lister - for GET with no name (list)\n- Watcher - for WATCH (watch)\n- Patcher - for PATCH (patch)\n\n### RBAC Authorization Enforcement\n\n**Authorization Decision** (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`)\n- RBACAuthorizer.Authorize() method checks if request verb matches PolicyRule.Verbs\n- Uses VerbMatches() helper for matching logic\n\n**Verb Matching Logic** (`pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go:26-35`)\n```go\nfunc VerbMatches(rule *rbacv1.PolicyRule, requestedVerb string) bool {\n  for _, ruleVerb := range rule.Verbs {\n    if ruleVerb == rbacv1.VerbAll { // \"*\" matches all verbs\n      return true\n    }\n    if ruleVerb == requestedVerb {\n      return true\n    }\n  }\n  return false\n}\n```\n\n**Verb Validation for ResourceNames** (`pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go:186-196`)\nWhen ResourceNames are specified, certain verbs are not allowed:\n- \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"deletecollection\" are blacklisted with ResourceNames\n- This prevents invalid authorization rules\n\n**Policy Rule Breakdown** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-helpers/auth/rbac/validation/policy_comparator.go:56-71`)\nBreakdownRule() decomposes complex rules into atomic verbs for comparison and validation\n\n### API Discovery and Resource Verb Exposure\n\n**APIResource Verb Field** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go:1203-1205`)\nEvery APIResource object includes:\n```\nVerbs: []string // list of supported kube verbs (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection, proxy)\n```\n\n**Discovery Helper** (`staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/discovery/helper.go:138-146`)\n- SupportsAllVerbs predicate filters resources by required verbs\n- Used by quota controller: GetQuotableResources filters for resources supporting [\"create\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n\n**APIResourceDiscovery Types** (`staging/src/k8s.io/api/apidiscovery/v2/types.go`, `pkg/apis/apidiscovery/types.go`)\nStructured discovery objects that include Verbs arrays for aggregated discovery endpoint\n\n### Custom Resource Verb Handling\n\n**CRD Discovery** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_discovery_controller.go`)\n- Builds verb lists from CRD spec.versions[].served and storage.storageClusters\n- Populates APIResource.Verbs for custom resources\n\n**CRD Handler Routes** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go:371-425`)\n- Router switches on verb string to route to appropriate handler\n- Supports: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection\n\n### Summary of Verb Coverage\n\nAll 8 standard verbs are comprehensively implemented:\n1. **get** - Single resource retrieval via Getter interface and GetResource handler\n2. **list** - Collection retrieval via Lister interface and ListResource handler  \n3. **watch** - Streaming changes via Watcher interface and ListResource handler with forceWatch=true\n4. **create** - Resource creation via Creater interface and CreateResource handler\n5. **update** - Full resource replacement via Updater interface and UpdateResource handler\n6. **patch** - Partial resource updates via Patcher interface and PatchResource handler\n7. **delete** - Single resource deletion via GracefulDeleter interface and DeleteResource handler\n8. **deletecollection** - Collection deletion via CollectionDeleter interface and DeleteCollection handler\n\nEach verb is:\n- Defined as a string constant and grouped in bootstrap policies\n- Mapped from HTTP methods in the discovery system\n- Implemented via specific storage interfaces that backends must satisfy\n- Enforced by RBAC authorization rules with matching logic\n- Exposed in API discovery for clients to discover supported operations\n- Validated in RBAC rules to prevent invalid configurations\n"
